The paper discusses a new stereo vision solution that uses a hybrid approach of classical stereo vision techniques and deep learning approaches. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on developing a solution suitable for embedded devices, which suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of deep learning also suggests that the paper may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
